title: Myles Standish State Forest Road Race
Massasoit Lung Challenge
description: The return of the Massasoit Lung Challenge Mountain Bike Race from the 1990’s was a long time coming but is now back for the 3rd year as a fundraiser for the American Lung Association. The traditional spring race works well with the sand based soil of cranberry land and has a tendency to dry out much quicker than other parts of New England.
course: The 7.1 mile course is a large clockwise loop with lots of fun single track, some fast double track and a very limited amount of smooth pavement. The terrain is most difficult in the early part of the loop before becoming more rolling in the middle with a couple of short kickers at the end.
registration: On line Registration ($25) is available on BikeReg.com. Day of registration will be located near the gatehouse on the paved road entering the Park. Day of registration fee add $10.

Go 2.7 miles and turn right (just after Gas Station) on Richmond St. Go 1.2 miles and turn right on Middleboro Ave. Massasoit will be on your left in .3 miles. From Route 495 in Middleboro take exit 5 to Route 18 South. Go .5 miles and turn right (sign for camping) on Taunton Ave. (becomes Middleboro Ave.) Go 2 miles and Massasoit will be on your left.

title: The Christina Clarke Genco Mother's Day Memori
CYCLE Kids Breakaway
description: In celebration of National Bike Month, CYCLE Kids is hosting a fundraising bike ride event on May 20, 2012 at the deCordova Museum in Lincoln, MA. The event will raise money for our mission of promoting healthy and active lifestyles for children through biking. A 62-mile bike ride will begin at 8:00 am, a 36-mile ride will begin at 10:00 am, and a 5-mile children’s ride will begin at 10:30 am. A gourmet luncheon provided by Chef Paul O’Connell of Chez Henri, open to bikers and non-bikers alike, will follow the rides at 12:30 pm in the deCordova Sculpture Garden.
course: 62 mile route, 36 mile route, 5 mile family route
directions: Ride starts and ends at the deCorvoda Museum at 51 Sandy Pond Road, Lincoln, MA 01773

title: ECV North Shore Time Trial Series
Ride Noho My First Road Bike Camp
Attleboro Bicycling Criterium and Kids Grass Crit
Fidelity Investments Gran Prix of Beverly
Tour of the Hilltowns
description:
The 14th Annual NCC Tour of the Hilltowns road race will take place on Saturday, July 21, 2012. 

This classic race promises to be a highlight of the 2012 season as it again challenges riders with the now infamous East Hawley Road climb and the long grind back to Notchview Reservation. 

The race is produced by the Northampton Cycling Club to benefit the NCC and the Notchview Reservation.
course: 155 km (97 mi) double loop with 3 major climbs and 2 feed zones for the Elite Men and 90km (57 mi) loop with two major climbs and one feed zone for all other categories. Start and finish at Notchview Reservation on Rt. 9 in Windsor, MA.
registration:
Entry fees increase $5 on July 6, 2012.

Entry Fee includes $3 for USAC insurance. 

Juniors race for $5 regardless of category entered. 

Masters races are Cat 1-4 only. Standard BikeReg fee applied to on line registration.
notes:
Held under USA Cycling event permit. All USA Cycling Rules apply; approved helmets are mandatory; no mountain bikes, aero bars or straight bars; shirts must have sleeves.

For more information visit http://www.nohobikeclub.org
directions: West on Route 9 from Northampton 29 miles to Windsor. Notchview Reservation is about one mile east of Windsor Center and Rt. 8A.

title: Roll In The Hay with BOB
QuadCross 2012
course: Start on the Soccer field, go up behind the pavilion, loop around some trees, through the pit, gravel and paved parking lot, 180 onto a gravel road, 180 onto a woods road, over the hill and through the woods, back through the pits, down to the lower level, around the sand pit, over the barriers, back into the soccer field.
registration: bikereg until the Friday before the race, Day of, many events will sell out, please register early.
notes: Parking at the venue will be tight. Do not park on Old MIll Road. There will be a Maynard Police Detail to enforce this.  If possible please make use of the overflow parking at Stratus Technology.

title: Bike Fest 2012 Tour of the Valley
course:
- Motorized SAG provided for century, metric century and 40 mile ride.
- SAG available for 25 mile and family rides with call (phone number on Cue Sheets).
- Improved course marking system for 2012
- Same great ride routes as 2011 with a few improvements for century, metric, and Orchard and Steph’s Farm.
- All new 8-mile family ride route with much less climbing.
- Up to three craft beers included with your lunch (no day-of beer sales.)
- Rides start en-mass with lead out from Look Park Ranger’s vehicle
registration:
Note: Fees increase on 9/12/2012. $10 more for Century, Metric, and Orchard. $5 more for Steph’s Farm Ride. 

Register before 9/12 and save.

Kids ride Free: Children 10 years old or younger ride free with a registered parent. Both child and parent must be present at packet pick up.

Please pre-register. Day of registration is an additional $10 (additional $5 for Steph’s Farm and Family rides). Pre-registration closes on 9/21 at 11:00pm.

Note: Look Park imposes a motor vehicle entry fee of $5. Free Parking is available at JFK Middle School on Bridge Road approximately 1/4 mile from the park entrance. Bicycles always enter free.
notes: All proceeds benefit Steph’s Wild Ride Children’s Cancer Foundation, the Northampton Education Foundation  and the Northampton Cycling Club’s youth and amateur cycling programs.  NCC is registered 501(c)3 charity.
